Dominik Vogt, Nov-1-1998:
-------------------------

At the moment, we have basically four types of copyright in our code:

1) GPL in some modules.
2) Copyright notices that state everything may be done with the code as long
   as the copyright stays intact.
3) The twm copyright. It states the same as 2).
4) Copyright by someone else without any permission.

Obviously 1) is no problem, and I think 2) and 3) are not either since these
notices grant us the right to redistribute the code under GPL (is that
correct?). The twm copyright is still in six files. Can I get a copy of the
original files somewhere to check what has to be done to remove the twm
copyright?

	fvwm/add_window.c
	fvwm/events.c
	fvwm/fvwm.h
	fvwm/menus.h
	fvwm/screen.h
	fvwm/fvwm2.man


The offending files or modules for 4) are:

	extras/FvwmPipe
		Matthias Ettrich (ettrich@informatik.uni-tuebingen.de)

	extras/FvwmWharf
		Bo Yang
		Frank Fejes
		Beat Christen
		Kaj Groner
		Alfredo K. Kojima
		Robert Nation

	extras/fvwmperl
		Dan Astoorian <djast@utopia.csas.com>

	extras/fvwmpython
		Barry A. Warsaw <bwarsaw@python.org>

	icons/xterm-bsd.xpm
		Marshall Kirk McKusicki

	modules/FvwmCascade
		Andrew Veliath

	modules/FvwmTile
		Andrew Veliath

In docs/m4_hacks there is a notice about a potential copyright problem with
twm code. Anybody who knows what code this refers to?

I have prepared the file archives/COPYING that puts all code except the
files mentioned above under GNU public license. This way, all future code
will be automatically placed under GPL so we can one by one resolve the
copyright issues still left until we have clean GPLed code.




